track.name: IF I SAY, I LOVE YOU

wiki.summary: 오늘만 I LOVE YOU (IF I SAY, I LOVE YOU)” is a first digital single by BOYNEXTDOOR, released on January 6th. It is a dance song that captures the realistic aftermath of a breakup. Woonhak and Taesan participated in the production of the song. ‘The lyrics are self-deprecating to the point of being somewhat pathetic, yet the melody, based on a band sound, is lively and upbeat. This contrast is a key point of the song. Although it’s a breakup song, it’s not overwhelmingly nostalgic or sad. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: 오늘만 I LOVE YOU (IF I SAY, I LOVE YOU)” is a first digital single by BOYNEXTDOOR, released on January 6th. It is a dance song that captures the realistic aftermath of a breakup. Woonhak and Taesan participated in the production of the song. ‘The lyrics are self-deprecating to the point of being somewhat pathetic, yet the melody, based on a band sound, is lively and upbeat. This contrast is a key point of the song. Although it’s a breakup song, it’s not overwhelmingly nostalgic or sad. The wit of BOYNEXTDOOR shines through as they portray the days following a breakup — when one lacks the courage to move on and feels like nothing is within their grasp — in a cheerful light.’ - Melon Read more on Last.fm.
